msContents.summary: A collection of edifying stories and anecdotes; the author attributes the majority of the work to borrowings from al-Sūyūtī who got it from Kamāl al-Dīn al-Humām (f. 1r). Some pages are out of place and some are missing; minor water damage.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in naskh in black ink; pointed, partially vocalized.

origin.p: Copy completed the 20th of Rabīʻ al-Ākhir in the year 1145 AH (f. 57v).
